snippet.textDisplay:
Hey everyone ,
The bottom line is he needs to get back to his weight when he was at Duke
It’s very clear he doesn’t have near the lift that he had at duke
Listen , I love Zion , I want him to succeed , this is gonna sound harsh but there’s a demon he has to defeat , and it’s food .
If he would follow the nutritionists guidelines he would have been 20 pounds lighter right now , even just swimming in the pool these last few months
I’m not saying it’s easy , and I’m rooting for him.
But the way he runs on the court and how he lands on one leg.... that’s ridiculous , he has to play on his instincts
I just hope he can develop a boxer’s mentality and get his body to the proper weight where he can be a force of nature like we all saw him at Duke
I’m concerned at the weight he is right now he’s susceptible to injury

snippet.textDisplay: IMO his game caters to the NBA much better than in College. He'll put up Lebron like numbers. I also think that his mentality seems to be that he wants to be well-rounded and associated with winning, so he'll end up having decent assist numbers too. Similar to Chris Webber probably. Main difference is he's more explosive than Webber. In College his ability to cover insane amounts of space when he picks up the ball didn't help as much because of how crowded it gets with less shooters and a smaller 3 pt line. In the NBA he'll be able to utilize that ability to take long strides and insanely long leaping layups. The dunks are great and everything, but those lays look unprecedented and unstoppable.
